Task 1: Understanding WHOIS and Certificate Transparency
Subtask 1.1: WHOIS Protocol Basics
WHOIS provides domain registration information including:

Registrar and registration dates
Name servers
Contact information
Domain status
Verify WHOIS installation:

which whois
# If not installed: sudo apt update && sudo apt install whois -y
Subtask 1.2: Certificate Transparency Overview
Certificate Transparency (CT) logs provide:

Public records of all issued SSL certificates
Historical certificate data
Subdomain discovery capabilities
Detection of unauthorized certificates
crt.sh is a web interface to CT logs allowing searches by domain, organization, or certificate fingerprint.

